collections.name: SteamPunk Pharaohs
collections.description:
SteamPunk Pharaohs merges ancient Egyptian royalty with Victorian-era industrial innovation, creating a visually striking blend of antiquity and machinery. 

Theme and Setting
Theme: Ancient Egyptian pharaohs rule a desert empire powered by steam-driven technology, blending mysticism with industrial revolution aesthetics.

Setting: Expansive desert cities feature towering brass pyramids, sand-filled factories, and railway networks connecting oasis hubs. The Nile is reimagined as a network of steam-powered aqueducts.

collections.name: Double Takes
collections.description:
"Made ya look!" In "Double Takes," the latest collaboration between frequently sold-out Orangehare artists Yuki and Klara, nothing is quite as it seems. Across 54 unique one-of-one pieces, figures flicker between selves—mirrored but not identical, reflected but slightly askew. Is it déjà vu, a trick of the eye, or something else entirely? Pulling from vintage film reels and the woodblock traditions of Korea and Japan, the collection unspools like a reel of lost memories—each frame a question, each double an answer that never quite resolves... because sometimes, the mirror looks BACK. Designed and brought to life through Orangehare’s in-house production process, Double Takes merges Yuki and Klara’s distinct styles of woodblock and encaustic printing into a seamless, cinematic whole.

Instagram: @orangehare.io
Twitter: @Orangehare_io

collections.name: M.Engel
collections.description:
人の心を動かすには、つまりは感動させるには・・・
私にできることは、いろんなことを考えてばかりで
自分が一番動けなくなっていた時、MOVE IT という言葉に出会いました。
育児は幸せばかりではなく、辛いことや孤独や不安と日々戦っている毎日です。でも全ては自分次第ということに気がつきました。綺麗事かもしれないし、気持ちの問題で解決できるようなことではないかもしれないけれど。
とにかく”動いてみて”欲しい、そうすれば何か、変わるかもしれない。そして私も同様、MOVE ITしていきたいと願いを込めて・・・
